claim.claim-text:
19. A method for detection and monitoring of a state of a lubricant of a bearing, comprising the following steps:
configuring a sample area and a receiver so that the receiver receives, from the sample area, diffuse reflection of electromagnetic radiation emitted by a transmitter, the sample area being arranged at least in places in an interior of the bearing that is filled with a lubricant;
irradiating, by the transmitter, a sample of the lubricant with electromagnetic radiation;
detecting, by the receiver from the diffusely reflected electromagnetic radiation, a spectrum of the sample in a range of a C—H combination mode in a near or middle infrared range; and
using the spectrum to measure a deterioration of the lubricant.
